314 MY FATHER IS OMNIPOTENT
1 My Father is omnipotent, 
 And that you can’t deny; 
 A God of might and miracles —  
 ‘Tis written in the sky. 
(C) It took a miracle to put the stars in place,  It took a miracle to hang the world in space;  But when he saved my soul, 
 Cleansed and made me whole, 
 It took a miracle of love and grace! 
2 Though here His glory has been shown,  We still can’t fully see 
 The wonders of His might, His throne —   ‘Twill take eternity. 
3 The Bible tells us of His power 
 And wisdom all way through, 
 And every little bird and flower 
 Are testimonies too.
315 慈爱怜悯祂来寻我
1 慈爱怜悯，祂来寻我，  降世为要将我得着。  祂从罪恶、羞耻深壑，  藉恩救拔了我。
和 从沉沦中，祂救拔我！  用祂慈手救拔了我！  今入光明，黑夜已过！  赞美主名，祂救拔我！ 
2 我不识祂，祂来召我，  激动我心，开我心锁，  发出恩言，免我罪过，  是祂救拔了我！ 
3 头上荆冕，将祂刺伤，  手脚被钉，枪扎肋旁！  赦我罪愆，担我忧伤，  祂爱救拔了我。 
4 我今住在安稳高处，  我魂深感安息、满足；  但我仍然无法说出：  为何祂救拔我。 
315 IN LOVING KINDNESS JESUS CAME
1 In loving kindness Jesus came 
 My soul in mercy to reclaim, 
 And from the depths of sin and shame 
 Thro’ grace He lifted me. 
(C) From sinking sand He lifted me, 
 With tender hand He lifted me, 
 From shades of night to plains of light, 
 Oh, praise His name, He lifted me! 
2 He called me long before I heard, 
 Before my sinful heart was stirred, 
 But when I took Him at His word, 
 Forgiv’n, He lifted me. 
3 His brow was pierced with many a thom, 
 His hands by cruel nails were tom, 
 When from my guilt and grief, forlorn, 
 In love He lifted me. 
4 Now on a higher plane I dwell, 
 And with my soul I know ‘tis well; 
 Yet how or why, I cannot tell, 
 He should have lifted me.
